Synopsis
    grep [OPTIONS] QUERY [FILE...]
    grep [OPTIONS] [-e QUERY | -f FILE] [FILE...]

Description
    grep searches the named input FILEs for lines containing a match to the given QUERY. By default, grep prints the matching lines.

Generic Program Information:
    --help
    Print a usage message briefly summarizing these command-line options and the bug-reporting address, then exit.

Options:
    Matching Control:
        -i, --ignore-case
        Ignore case distinctions in the QUERY.

    General Output Control:
        -l, --files-with-matches
        Suppress normal output; instead print the name of each input file from which output would normally have been printed. The scanning will stop on the first match.